node.title: Victoria has recorded 1,196 new local COVID-19 cases and three deaths
node.alt: A tram in the Melbourne CBD
node.description: There are now 9,774 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 482 people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,196\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and three\u00a0deaths, as the number of hospitalised patients continues to fall.", "There are now 9,774\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 482\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.", "There are 284\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 52\u00a0are in intensive care and 29\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 53\u00a0people were in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 72,754\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 3,358\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "Victoria has now fully vaccinated more than 89 per cent\u00a0of its 12+ population.", "More to come.", "", "
